    {
      "id": "QqncIYfq27C0UovpOKLY1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2542.4310344523064,
      "y": 250.31244029260858,
      "width": 793.039306640625,
      "height": 1225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bhx",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1697886379,
      "version": 1178,
      "versionNonce": 528706181,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783773102632,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Deep dives:\n1. Scale and availability\n    Aggregation\n2. Recalculation\n3. Reconciliation\n\n\n1. Scale and availability\nmulti-region deployments\nmulti AZs\nDB : aurora\nEKS for services with auto-scaling\n\nscale:\nsvcs\ningestion: horizontal scalaing\naggregation svc:\nhas state:\n    store previous state in DB\n    use only in case of svc going down\n    so when svc goes down we first populate state from DB and then aggregate\n    for aggregate, we can use, map reduce kind of functionality\n    scale svc by aggregation types\nif batch : map reduce\nif streaming : spark streaming\n\nkafka\n    partition by tenantid, adId\ndb\n    PK (Partition: tenantid, adId, ck: timestamp)\n    replication : leaderless replication and gossip protocol\n\nhandle \nduplicates: idempotency\nlate events: \n    use eventClickTimestamp\n    use processTimestamp\nwe will use eventClickedTimestamp for accuracy\n\nquery 1:\nnumber of ads in 1 min\nuse tumbling window of 1 min\n\nquery 2:\ntop 100 ads in last x mins\nuse sliding wondow for x mins\n\nReconciliation:\nuse reconciliation process to match data between raw data and aggregated data",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Deep dives:\n1. Scale and availability\n    Aggregation\n2. Recalculation\n3. Reconciliation\n\n\n1. Scale and availability\nmulti-region deployments\nmulti AZs\nDB : aurora\nEKS for services with auto-scaling\n\nscale:\nsvcs\ningestion: horizontal scalaing\naggregation svc:\nhas state:\n    store previous state in DB\n    use only in case of svc going down\n    so when svc goes down we first populate state from DB and then aggregate\n    for aggregate, we can use, map reduce kind of functionality\n    scale svc by aggregation types\nif batch : map reduce\nif streaming : spark streaming\n\nkafka\n    partition by tenantid, adId\ndb\n    PK (Partition: tenantid, adId, ck: timestamp)\n    replication : leaderless replication and gossip protocol\n\nhandle \nduplicates: idempotency\nlate events: \n    use eventClickTimestamp\n    use processTimestamp\nwe will use eventClickedTimestamp for accuracy\n\nquery 1:\nnumber of ads in 1 min\nuse tumbling window of 1 min\n\nquery 2:\ntop 100 ads in last x mins\nuse sliding wondow for x mins\n\nReconciliation:\nuse reconciliation process to match data between raw data and aggregated data",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
